    "rationale": "Coverage-gap fix: the worst-served precincts are concentrated in the far northeast corner. Current max assigned distance is precinct 78 at 2.98 km, and nearest-open analysis among opened sites shows the northeast tail is anchored by site 9 at (7.25,7.77). Testing closed candidates for the worst precincts shows site 24 cuts those distances sharply (e.g. precinct 78 from 2.98 km assigned / 2.98 km nearest-open to 0.90 km to site 24; precinct 57 to 0.62 km; precinct 73 to 0.33 km) while remaining in the same corner. Closing site 9 keeps the site budget unchanged and lets the MILP rebalance globally around a much better northeast location."
